\exp \left( \frac{i \theta}{2} \sum_{h \in M_4} (z \cup z)_h \right ) = \mathbf{Z}_{\mathcal{M}_3}^{k}[z', z_0]

where:
- $\mathcal{M}_3 = \partial M_4$ is the boundary three-manifold;
- $z' = \sum_{i=1}^m q_i \delta(\mathcal{R}_i)$ is a sum of $m$ Dirac sheets representing the 't~Hooft loop insertion, each $q_i = \pm 1$;
- $z_0$ is a coclosed sum of (possibly disconnected) closed 2-surfaces on the boundary, representing the remaining part of $z$;
- $k$ is an integer satisfying $m \theta = 2\pi k$.

The explicit boundary partition function is:
\[
\mathbf{Z}_{\mathcal{M}_3}^{k}[z',z_0]=
\exp\left(\frac{i k \pi}{m} \sum_{c \in \mathcal{M}_3} (z_0 \cup_1 z')_c \right) 
\left(\prod_{\ell \in \Lambda_1(\mathcal{M}_3)} \frac{1}{m} \sum_{c_{\ell}=0}^{m-1}\right)
\prod_{p \in \Lambda_2(\mathcal{M}_3)} \delta_m \left[ (\dd c - z')_p \right]
\exp \left( -\frac{i k \pi}{m} \sum_{c \in \mathcal{M}_3} \left( -c \cup \dd c + z' \cup c + c \cup z' + 2c \cup z_0 \right)_c \right )
\]
where:
- $\Lambda_1(\mathcal{M}_3)$ is the set of oriented links (1-cells) on $\mathcal{M}_3$;
- $\Lambda_2(\mathcal{M}_3)$ is the set of oriented plaquettes (2-cells) on $\mathcal{M}_3$;
- $c_{\ell} \in \{0,1,...,m-1\}$ are $\mathbb{Z}_m$-valued 1-cochain variables on links $\ell$ of $\mathcal{M}_3$;
- $\dd c$ denotes the coboundary of $c$, i.e., $\dd c$ is the 2-cochain defined by $ (\dd c)_{p} = \sum_{\ell \in \partial p} c_{\ell}$ mod $m$ for each plaquette $p$;
- $z'$ and $z_0$ are $\mathbb{Z}$-valued 2-cochains supported on plaquettes of $\mathcal{M}_3$; $z'_p$ and $z_{0,p}$ denote their values on $p$;
- $\delta_m[X]$ is $1$ if $X \equiv 0 \pmod{m}$, and $0$ otherwise;
- $\cup$ denotes the cup product (with $\mathbb{Z}_m$ addition) between lattice cochains;
- $\cup_1$ denotes the higher cup-1 product (see e.g. Steenrod squares or standard cohomology), which detects intersection pairing between cochains;
- The sums $\sum_{c \in \mathcal{M}_3}$ mean $\sum_{\sigma} (\cdots)_{\sigma}$ over cells $\sigma$ of the appropriate dimension (as dictated by the cup product structure).

This partition function $\mathbf{Z}_{\mathcal{M}_3}^k[z',z_0]$ thus expresses the exponential of the $z \cup z$ bulk term exactly as a boundary-only functional involving cochains, cup products, and the auxiliary sum over $c_{\ell}$. All variables and terms are fully explicit and defined above.

